libsupertone is a comprehensive library specifically engineered
to facilitate the generation and detection of supervisory tones
used in telecommunication systems worldwide. These tones, which
include various call progress tones, busy signals, and other
signaling sounds, are crucial for indicating call status and
managing connections across diverse global telephony networks.
By providing robust support for a wide array of international
tone standards, libsupertone enables developers to create
applications that can accurately interpret and produce these
essential audio signals, ensuring compatibility and reliable
operation in a global communication context.
